Police swoop in on suspects allegedly linked to the murder of two Durban metro police officers. DURBAN - Three suspects have been arrested in connection with the murder of two Metro Police officers.
Sunday's shooting took place outside Durban councillor Moses Zulu's Phoenix house. READ: Hawks hunt killers of Durban police officers The officers were assigned there to protect Zulu, who had been receiving death threats. Police say the suspects were found in KwaMashu's M-section. READ: Durban councillor scared after police officers shot dead outside home Officials say the suspects could be linked to other crimes.